						<summary>

						

						<p>Slab in the temple of Dantēśvarī.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Jagadēkabhūshaṇa-mahā[rāju*] Śaka 984: 1062 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged record furnishes the details of date viz., Śaka 984, Āshāḍha, Thursday which are not sufficient for verification.</p>						

						<p>It states that when the king was camping <hi rend="italic">(nelevīḍu)</hi> at the place called Dattavāḍa, he made a gift of thirty <hi rend="italic">māḍas.</hi> The details of the grant, the donee or the temple, etc., are not clear.</p>						

						<p>(Published in <hi rend="italic">South Indian Inscriptions,</hi> Vol. X, No. 646).</p>						

						</summary>
